# Pentagon with three exactly collinear vertices (v1 v2 v3).
# The polygon's total area is large so AddMesh does not ignore it, but the
# ear-clipping triangulator ends with the collinear trio and emits an
# exactly-zero-area triangle that enters the chart pipeline. This used to be
# able to starve the ClusteredCharts seed selection (zero-area planar region)
# and hang; the fix falls back to seeding with the first unassigned face.
# The face deliberately starts at v4 so the triangulator's projection basis
# (built from the first three corners) is non-degenerate.
v 0 0 0
v 1 0 0
v 2 0 0
v 2.05 3 0
v -0.05 3 0
f 4 5 1 2 3
